<paragraph id="8BD136E8314CC01B4CDE8E5CFEF47701" blockId="5.[168,779,193,939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis id="B91AEAFA314CC01B4CDE8E5CFCD974D9" box="[168,778,371,395]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B91AEAFA314CC01B4CDE8E5CFE9974D9" bold="true" box="[168,330,371,395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Identification.</emphasis>
This is the first specific record of 
<emphasis id="B91AEAFA314CC01B4EC48E5BFCD974D9" box="[690,778,371,395]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">B. beck-</emphasis>
</emphasis>
ianum from 
<collectingRegion id="49AAF80A314CC01B4D478EBBFEBB74FE" box="[305,360,404,428]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Acre</collectingRegion>
. Despite being within the species’ expected distribution (it is common in Latin America), the present record is actually an extension of the species’ known distribution within 
<collectingCountry id="F3797678314CC01B4DA58ED7FDCB7742" box="[467,536,504,528]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, given that its closest known record was previously from 
<collectingRegion id="49AAF80A314CC01B4E478D35FD4F7763" box="[561,668,538,562]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Pará state</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B19314CC01B4EDA8D36FECF7701" author="Birckolz CJ &amp; Salvador RB &amp; Cavallari DC &amp; Simone LRL" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" pagination="133 - 150" refId="ref8006" refString="Birckolz CJ, Salvador RB, Cavallari DC, Simone LRL (2016) Illustrated checklist of newly described (2006 - 2016) land and fresh- water Gastropoda from Brazil. Archiv fur Molluskenkunde 145: 133 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / arch. moll / 145 / 133 - 150" type="journal article" year="2016">Birckolz et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136E8314CC01B4CDE8D4DFEF777AD" blockId="5.[168,779,193,939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis id="B91AEAFA314CC01B4CDE8D4DFE95772B" bold="true" box="[168,326,609,634]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">
<typeStatus id="54D5884A314CC01B4CDE8D4DFF307728" box="[168,227,610,634]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Type</typeStatus>
locality.
</emphasis>
Opara Island, Polynesia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B19314CC01B4E1F8D4EFD2D772B" author="Pfeiffer L" box="[617,766,609,633]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" refId="ref9448" refString="Pfeiffer L (1846). Symbolae ad historiam Heliceorum. Vol. 3. Th. Fischeri, Casselis, 100 pp." type="book" year="1846">Pfeiffer 1846</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B19314CC01B4CDE8DACFE9677C9" author="Pilsbry HA" box="[168,325,643,667]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" pagination="161 - 272" refId="ref9507" refString="Pilsbry HA (1906) Achatinidae: Stenogyrinae and Coeliaxinae. Manual of Conchology, Structural and Systematic, with Illustrations of the Species (Second Series: Pulmonata) 18: 161 - 272." type="journal article" year="1906">Pilsbry (1906)</bibRefCitation>
considered this locality mistaken, arguing that Pfeiffer’s specimens were most similar to those from Central America (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B19314CC01B4DD08DEAFD1B778F" author="Salvador RB &amp; Simone LRL" box="[422,712,709,733]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref9816" refString="Salvador RB, Simone LRL (2015) Taxonomical study on a sample of land snails from Alcobaca (Bahia, Brazil), with description of a new species. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde 8: 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="2015">
<collectingCountry id="F3797678314CC01B4DD08DEAFDD5778F" box="[422,518,709,733]" name="El Salvador" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Salvador</collectingCountry>
and Simone 2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B19314CC01B4EA58DEAFECA77AD" author="Silva FS &amp; Simone LRL &amp; Salvador RB" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" pagination="175 - 190" refId="ref10030" refString="Silva FS, Simone LRL, Salvador RB (2019) Taxonomic study on a collection of terrestrial mollusks from the region of Santa Maria, Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil. Arquivos de Zoologia 50: 175 - 190. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / 2176 - 7793 / 2019.50.03" type="journal article" year="2019">Silva et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3746563314CC01B4CDE8C22FEA876F9" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD136E8314CC01B4CDE8C22FEA876F9" blockId="5.[168,779,193,939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis id="B91AEAFA314CC01B4CDE8C22FEEE7677" bold="true" box="[168,317,781,805]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F3797678314CC01B4D328C22FE457677" box="[324,406,781,805]" name="Mexico" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F3797678314CC01B4DCD8C22FE2D7677" box="[443,510,781,805]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49AAF80A314CC01B4E7B8C21FDEC7674" box="[525,575,782,806]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Pará</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="49AAF80A314CC01B4E128C21FD007677" box="[612,723,781,806]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, Fernando de Noronha), including the Caribbean Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B19314CC01B4E9D8C00FEF7763A" author="Simone LRL" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" refId="ref10152" refString="Simone LRL (2006) Land and freshwater molluscs of Brazil. Editora Grafica Bernardi &amp; Fundacao de Amparo a Pesquisas do Estado de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, Brazil, 399 pp." type="book" year="2006">Simone 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B19314CC01B4D598C7FFDD5763A" author="Birckolz CJ &amp; Salvador RB &amp; Cavallari DC &amp; Simone LRL" box="[303,518,848,872]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" pagination="133 - 150" refId="ref8006" refString="Birckolz CJ, Salvador RB, Cavallari DC, Simone LRL (2016) Illustrated checklist of newly described (2006 - 2016) land and fresh- water Gastropoda from Brazil. Archiv fur Molluskenkunde 145: 133 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / arch. moll / 145 / 133 - 150" type="journal article" year="2016">Birckolz et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). It has been introduced to Hawaii and to greenhouses in Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B19314CC01B4EF68C5EFCD576D8" author="Cowie RH" box="[640,774,881,906]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" pagination="1 - 66" refId="ref8430" refString="Cowie RH (1997) Catalog and bibliography of the nonindigenous nonmarine snails and slugs of the Hawaiian Islands. Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 50: 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="1997">Cowie 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B19314CC01B4CDE8CBCFEA376F9" author="Horsak M &amp; Naggs F &amp; Backeljau T" box="[168,368,915,939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" pagination="123 - 130" refId="ref8800" refString="Horsak M, Naggs F, Backeljau T (2020) Paropeas achatinaceum (Pfeiffer, 1846) and other alien subulinine and opeatine land snails in European greenhouses (Gastropoda, Achatinidae). Malacologia 63: 123 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.4002 / 040.063.0112" type="journal article" year="2020">Horsák et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
